About a week after I moved in,

02:39.093 --> 02:41.927
I was in the bathroom,
getting ready for bed,

02:41.929 --> 02:45.531
and I saw a little,
black shadow about that high,

02:45.533 --> 02:48.700
-[Amy] Mm-hmm.
-run past the bathroom door.

02:48.702 --> 02:50.135
It scared me, so I left.

02:50.137 --> 02:52.004
-[Leanne] That was like
the first day.
-That was it.

02:52.006 --> 02:52.971
-Yeah, you were done.
-That was it.

02:52.973 --> 02:55.374
So, then I got
a contractor in here.

02:55.376 --> 02:58.010
He worked for about
three weeks.

02:58.012 --> 03:00.379
I came home one lunch break,

03:00.381 --> 03:02.347
and he was backing out
of the driveway.

03:02.349 --> 03:06.185
-[Amy] Mm-hmm.
-And he told me that
my house was haunted.

03:06.187 --> 03:09.087
[Leanne] And he was never
coming back in here
and he was so sorry.

03:09.089 --> 03:11.723
And he left like
$3,000 worth of tools.

03:11.725 --> 03:13.091
-Wow!
-[Leanne] Just left.

03:13.093 --> 03:15.060
[Amy] And what did he...
Did he say what happened?

03:15.062 --> 03:17.029
[Leanne] He wouldn't tell me,
he wouldn't talk about it,

03:17.031 --> 03:19.198
he just... he just fled.

03:19.200 --> 03:20.832
-Wow!
-[Leanne] And he just left.

03:20.834 --> 03:24.970
Then, I mean, it would really
just be constant
thumping, walking.

03:24.972 --> 03:27.940
Sounds like there's people
in the kitchen all the time.

03:27.942 --> 03:29.841
The TV goes on.

03:29.843 --> 03:31.243
Lights will go on and off.

03:31.245 --> 03:33.278
[Amy] Now, how many
square-feet is this house?

03:33.280 --> 03:35.247
925.

03:35.249 --> 03:38.951
-So all of this is happening
in a 925-square-foot home.
-You can't get away from it.

03:39.386 --> 03:41.587
I mean, that's insane to me.

03:41.589 --> 03:45.390
-And now, can you...
-[Adam] Yeah.

03:45.392 --> 03:48.594
-[Adam] I heard that. Did
you hear that creaking sound?
-Yeah. What's that sound?

03:49.363 --> 03:50.996
What is that?

03:50.998 --> 03:54.032
-It's the house. Mm-hmm.
-[Amy] It's like scratching.

03:54.034 --> 03:58.237
Can we move and see
a little bit more of this
section and keep talking?

03:58.239 --> 04:00.639
-[Leanne] Yeah.
-Just kinda show us around.

04:01.842 --> 04:03.942
[Leanne] A lot of activity
happens in this hallway.

04:03.944 --> 04:05.877
Um, there's always,
like, footsteps.

04:05.879 --> 04:07.446
This is the room
I got shoved in.

04:07.448 --> 04:09.848
I was standing here
on the 20th, doing some stuff,

04:09.850 --> 04:11.483
my mom was like here,

04:11.485 --> 04:15.821
and something just pushed
my spine into,
like, this doorknob.

04:15.823 --> 04:17.356
-[Amy] Wow!
-And it was hard.

04:17.358 --> 04:19.157
I don't wanna say push.
It's like shoved.

04:19.159 --> 04:21.059
That's violent.

04:21.061 --> 04:24.429
[Leanne] It was...
And I've never been touched
in the house until that point.

04:24.431 --> 04:26.231
Really? And so that was...

04:26.233 --> 04:28.300
Gosh, only like 11 days ago.

04:28.302 --> 04:30.769
-Mm-hmm. Right.
-And you knew we were
coming at that point.

04:30.771 --> 04:33.305
So now, I'm even more, like,
I hate this room.

04:33.307 --> 04:34.673
-[Amy] Mmm.
-I just hate this room.

04:34.675 --> 04:36.375
You don't have to be in there.

04:36.377 --> 04:38.977
-[Amy] Yeah, come on out.
-[Leanne] There's something
not right in that room.

04:38.979 --> 04:40.379
Do you want to show us
these rooms?

04:40.381 --> 04:42.814
-This is my bedroom.
-[Amy] Okay.

04:42.816 --> 04:44.516
I mean,
it feels light and airy.

04:44.518 --> 04:46.485
-It's nice and lit.
-[Adam] Yeah!

04:46.487 --> 04:49.254
We have to wait
till nighttime, so.

04:49.256 --> 04:54.893
I sound crazy, but I swear,
when it gets dark,
the house changes.

04:54.895 --> 04:56.228
[Amy] Really? Okay.

04:56.230 --> 04:59.898
It's like something just...
nasty is here.

04:59.900 --> 05:01.466
Things just get different.

05:01.468 --> 05:03.201
-Okay.
-[Leanne] One night
I was here,

05:03.203 --> 05:05.537
scared as usual,
and I sleep with
the lights on,

05:05.539 --> 05:08.006
I never sleep
in the dark, ever.

05:08.008 --> 05:10.509
And something shook my bed.

05:11.278 --> 05:14.179
And I looked,
and he... it let me see it.

05:14.181 --> 05:16.882
Little, black shadow,
looks like he's wearing
a hood,

05:16.884 --> 05:19.284
standing right where
you are actually.

05:19.286 --> 05:20.852
And it just stayed there,

05:20.854 --> 05:23.455
and then vanished, like,
maybe two seconds later.

05:23.457 --> 05:25.590
Do you always sleep
with the lights on?

05:25.592 --> 05:28.327
Or only sleep
with the lights on here?

05:28.329 --> 05:29.961
Only here.

05:29.963 --> 05:33.198
When did the bed shaking
and the little, tiny
shadow figure show up?

05:33.200 --> 05:34.266
[Leanne] That was like
last month,

05:34.268 --> 05:35.867
but it's happened before that.

05:35.869 --> 05:38.203
Like, they just
do it randomly.
I don't...

05:38.205 --> 05:40.839
-And who's room is that?
-[Leanne] That's my mom's.

05:40.841 --> 05:43.141
-Okay.
-[Amy] Let's check it out.

05:43.143 --> 05:45.010
-[Amy] So this is
your mom's room.
-[Leanne] Yes.

05:45.012 --> 05:47.879
[Leanne] She's seen lots
and lots and lots of stuff.

05:47.881 --> 05:49.381
But she's not scared like you?

05:49.383 --> 05:51.550
She doesn't really sleep
at night anymore.

05:51.552 --> 05:53.318
[Amy] She doesn't?
What does she do?

05:53.320 --> 05:54.353
She hasn't, for years.

05:54.355 --> 05:57.089
She watches TV
with all the lights on.

05:57.091 --> 05:59.224
-And then she sleeps
during the day?
-[Leanne] Yeah.

05:59.226 --> 06:01.893
-Oh, okay.
-So she's scared, but she...

06:01.895 --> 06:04.196
You know, and I tell her,
I'm like, "We can sell it."

06:04.198 --> 06:05.330
And she's just like, "No!"

06:05.332 --> 06:07.933
She's like, "I refuse
to let them win."

06:09.169 --> 06:11.203
I mean... Yeah, I get it.

06:11.205 --> 06:13.071
She's sort of letting
them win though,

06:13.073 --> 06:16.341
-when she has to alter--
-And stay up till
5 o'clock in the morning.

06:16.343 --> 06:17.342
-Yeah.
-[Amy] Yeah, she does.

06:17.344 --> 06:18.877
Has anything happened
to her that's--

06:18.879 --> 06:20.912
[Leanne] Yeah, here.
In this room.

06:20.914 --> 06:22.948
-[Adam] What?
-Um, she had a heart attack,

06:22.950 --> 06:27.352
and she was actually dead
for about five minutes.

06:27.354 --> 06:29.888
They had to break a few ribs
to bring her back.

06:29.890 --> 06:31.356
They almost didn't
bring her back.

06:31.358 --> 06:32.891
-[Adam] Oh, my [bleep]
-That happened in here?

06:32.893 --> 06:35.193
[Leanne] Uh-huh. In 2014.

06:35.195 --> 06:40.465
Did the activity for her,
specifically, increase
after that incident?

06:40.467 --> 06:43.034
No, it's been here
all along since she moved in.

06:43.036 --> 06:44.703
-[Adam] Okay.
-[Amy] We definitely need
to chat with her.

06:44.705 --> 06:46.138
All right, well,
that is a lot.

06:46.140 --> 06:48.206
I mean, it sounds like,
this is one of those
cases where, like...

06:48.208 --> 06:51.143
